description:
Subjects Addressed: (1) Ten literal days before the Day of Atonement, trumpets were blown. (7:00)
(2) Discover the meaning of the blowing of trumpets. (12:07)
(3) Ten years before the opening of the Antitypical Day of Atonement, William Miller and his associates began to blow the trumpets. (16:43)
(4) Discover the connection between the blowing of trumpets at Mount Sinai and the blowing of trumpets leading up to the Day of Atonement. (20:40)
(5) William Miller and his associates only preached the first and second angels’ messages leading up the opening of the Day of Atonement in 1844. The Seventh-day Adventist movement was raised up to preach the three angels’ messages, with emphasis on the third angel, to usher in the close of the Day of Atonement. (30:10)
(6) The third angel’s message show that God’s commandment-keeping people will encounter close combat, a battle, a war, with the Beast and its Image. Therefore, Seventh-day Adventists must blow trumpets and sound an alarm. (33:00)
(7) The Lord prophesied that His professed people will reject the trumpet messages and the sound of the alarm. (41:45)
(8) Consider the current events that show that the Mark of the Beast is near. (44:45)
(9) The Bible teaches that God’s end time messengers must blow the trumpet and sound the alarm in both the church and the world. (54:35)
(10) The Bible shows us that once the trumpet and the alarm messages are accepted by the people, Jesus will pour out the Latter Rain, prepare us to combat the king of north, and close the Investigative Judgment. (1:01:30)
(11) The Bible teaches that when the trumpets and alarm were blown, God’s people must take their journey. Discover the spiritual journey that we all must take.
